<paragraph blockId="37.[163,779,346,982]" pageId="37" pageNumber="392">
<emphasis box="[163,575,346,368]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="392">
Diagnosis: 
<taxonomicName box="[297,575,346,367]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Odontobuthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="37" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tavighiae">Odontobuthus tavighiae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
can be separated from other species of the genus by the following combination of characters. Scorpions of medium to large size, adults 
<quantity box="[416,543,438,460]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.95" metricValueMax="6.7" metricValueMin="5.2" pageId="37" pageNumber="392" unit="mm" value="59.5" valueMax="67.0" valueMin="52.0">52–67 mm</quantity>
(
<specimenCount box="[562,578,441,459]" pageId="37" pageNumber="392" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
) and 
<quantity box="[652,778,438,460]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" metricValueMax="7.9" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="37" pageNumber="392" unit="mm" value="62.0" valueMax="79.0" valueMin="45.0">45–79 mm</quantity>
(
<specimenCount box="[172,187,472,490]" pageId="37" pageNumber="392" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
) (
<figureCitation box="[214,296,469,491]" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="31.[163,243,1573,1595]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,195,1533]" captionTargetId="figure-127@31.[323,1283,195,1533]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figure 18. Odontobuthus tavighiae. Habitus, dorsal aspect (A, C), ventral aspect (B, D). A, B, ♀ (ZMFUM 1362). C, D, ♂ (ZMFUM 1364). Scale bars = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6600025" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6600025/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="392">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). Colour yellow. Median ocular tubercle situated in anterior half of carapace, distance from anterior carapace margin, 0.34–0.38. Pedipalp chela movable finger long relative to manus (
<collectionCode box="[661,721,561,582]" pageId="37" pageNumber="392">MFL</collectionCode>
/ 
<collectionCode box="[730,773,561,582]" country="France" name="Musee de Lectoure" pageId="37" pageNumber="392">ML</collectionCode>
, 1.69–2.06). Median denticle rows of pedipalp chela fixed and movable fingers each comprising 13 or 14 oblique subrows of denticles. Pectinal tooth count, 30–34 (
<specimenCount box="[248,264,687,705]" pageId="37" pageNumber="392" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
) and 22–27 (
<specimenCount box="[417,432,687,705]" pageId="37" pageNumber="392" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
). Ventrosubmedian carinae of metasomal segments II and III each with two pairs of tooth-like processes (
<figureCitation box="[401,495,745,767]" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="35.[163,242,1638,1660]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,195,1598]" captionTargetId="figure-101@35.[323,1283,195,1598]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="Figure 22. Odontobuthus. Metasomal segments II and III, lateral aspect. A, Odontobuthus bidentatus ♀ (ZMFUM 2061). B, Odontobuthus brevidigitus ♂ (ZMFUM 1438). C, Odontobuthus doriae ♀ (ZMFUM 2014). D, Odontobuthus odonturus ♀ (ZMFUM 1439).E, Odontobuthus tavighiae ♀ (ZMFUM 2074).F, Odontobuthus tirgari ♂ (ZMFUM 1398).Scale bars = 2.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6600036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6600036/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="392">Fig. 22E</figureCitation>
). Metasomal segment IV length to width (L/W), 1.60–1.95. Ventrolateral carinae of metasomal segment 
<collectionCode box="[424,442,807,828]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="37" pageNumber="392" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
with three or four prominent lobate processes; anal arch with three large lobes laterally; posteroventral margin of segment 
<collectionCode box="[663,681,868,889]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="37" pageNumber="392" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
with six reduced lobes. Telson small, narrow, length to width (TL/W), 1.89–2.28 and length to height (TL/H), 1.96– 2.35 (
<figureCitation box="[226,326,960,982]" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="33.[163,245,1382,1404]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,195,1342]" captionTargetId="figure-212@33.[323,1283,195,1342]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figure 20. Odontobuthus. Metasomal segment V, lateral aspect. A, Odontobuthus bidentatus ♀ (ZMFUM 2061) B, Odontobuthus brevidigitus ♂ (ZMFUM–1438). C, Odontobuthus doriae ♀ (ZMFUM 2014). D, Odontobuthus odonturus ♀ (ZMFUM 1439). E, Odontobuthus tavighiae ♀ (ZMFUM–2074). F, Odontobuthus tirgari ♂ (ZMFUM 1398). Scale bars = 2.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6600029" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6600029/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="392">Figs 20E</figureCitation>
